    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA43-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu pirivuṇarttappaṭṭa tōḻi talaivaṉaic celavu aḻuṅkuvittatu (EV: colliyatu).</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is who the confidante who had been informed about the separation prevented HIM from going.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA43">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            tukilvirit taṉṉa veyilavi ruruppi</l>
<l>            ṉeṉṟūḻ nīṭiya kuṉṟattuk kavāa</l>
<l>            ṉōypacic cennā yuyaṅkumarai tolaicci</l>
<l>            yārntaṉa voḻinta miccil cēynāṭ</l>
<l>            ṭaruñcurañ celvōrkku valci yākum </l>
<l>            vemmai yāriṭai yiṟatta ṉumakkē</l>
<l>            meymmali yuvakai yākiṉ ṟivaṭkē</l>
<l>            yañca leṉṟa viṟaikai viṭṭeṉap</l>
<l>            paiṅkaṇ yāṉai vēntupuṟat tiṟuttaliṟ</l>
<l>            kaḷaiyunark kāṇātu kalaṅkiya vuṭaimati </l>
<l>            lōreyiṉ maṉṉaṉ pōla</l>
<l>            vaḻivuvan taṉṟā loḻital kēṭṭē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Traversing the hot [and] difficult ways,</l>
<l rend="indent">where for those who are going through the difficult desert</l>
<l rend="indent">in a distant land food is the left-overs that stayed behind</l>
<l rend="indent">from those who had filled themselves<note place="foot">Here <term xml:lang="ta">ārntaṉa</term> has to read as a participial noun in apposition to <term xml:lang="ta">cennāy</term> of the line before.</note> having killed</l>
<l rend="indent">an exhausted wild cow: the red dogs in painful hunger,</l>
<l rend="indent2">on the hilly slopes where the sun has been lasting,</l>
<l rend="indent2">in the form of blazing heat like fine cloth spread out,</l>
<l>– to you it has become a pleasure in which your body rejoices.</l>
<l rend="indent4">To her,</l>
<l rend="indent3">having heard of [her] staying behind,</l>
<l rend="indent4">it has come as ruin,</l>
<l rend="indent2">as to the king with one fortress with breaking fortifications,</l>
<l rend="indent">agitated since he doesn't see anyone to relieve him</l>
<l rend="indent">from the king waiting outside with green-eyed elephants,</l>
<l>because the monarch who had said “don't be afraid” has deserted [him].</l>
        </lg>
